author: codex-maintainer
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: 1) Untracked pm issue/history files are audited for secrets or private data. 2) Safe files are committed and pushed. 3) The commit excludes unrelated local-only tracker files if any remain unsafe or unrelated.
definition_of_ready: Imported untracked pm issue/history files are present in the worktree and their origin is understood.
goal: Tracker completeness
objective: Version imported pm issue/history records safely
value: Keeps repository pm data complete and reproducible
impact: Dependabot-derived tracker items and histories become part of the repo state
outcome: Imported pm issues/history are committed without leaking private data
why_now: The user explicitly wants the imported issue/history files tracked in git.
risk: medium
confidence: medium
component: "tracker:pm-data"
customer_impact: Repository users can inspect current security-tracker items directly from git history.
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-03-12T23:13:24.830Z",codex-maintainer,Audit imported tracker files for private data before committing them.
  "2026-03-12T23:14:13.187Z",codex-maintainer,"Audited 13 imported issue files and 13 matching history logs. No credentials, tokens, private keys, JWT-like strings, emails, or auth-token assignments were found. Content is limited to Dependabot advisory metadata, package paths, and repository alert reference URLs."
  "2026-03-12T23:14:31.109Z",codex-maintainer,"Evidence: staged imported issue/history files passed node scripts/check-secrets.mjs, targeted regex audit found no credentials/private keys/JWT-like strings/emails, and git diff --cached --check reported no whitespace or patch-format issues."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-03-12T23:13:24.830Z",codex-maintainer,Use pm as the system of record while preserving append-only item history.
